cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper discusses the transportation of video content in a VOD system, which involves network infrastructure and multimedia content. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses chunk selection policies and peer-to-peer networks, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The proposed hybrid architecture also involves search mechanisms, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses interactive operations, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). However, since the paper focuses more on the technical aspects of the system rather than the user interface, cs.MM is less likely than the other categories mentioned.
